dc_title_s: Poland 1:100,000. Osterode, sheet L-14. A.M.S. M651 (G.S.G.S. 4416)
dc_description_s: AMS 2. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4416. Alternate title: Osterode, Germany. Polyconic projection. Russian belt 4 grid. Relief shown by 10 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. With a glossary. Compiled from Germany, 1:25,000, German General Staff, 1910-36; Germany 1:100,000, German General Staff, Sheet 43, 1933; Poland, 1:100,000, Military Geographic Institute, Sheets 34-29, 1930; 34-30, 1932; 35-29, 1930 and 35-30, 1929. Roads in Poland classified from British intelligence reports, 1943. Map states location as Germany though the map actually depicts Poland.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
